    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For values exactly halfway between rounded decimal values, NumPy\nrounds to the nearest even value. Thus 1.5 and 2.5 round to 2.0,\n-0.5 and 0.5 round to 0.0, etc."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/numpy/rint/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "rint",
              "text": "flops.round"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " uses a fast but sometimes inexact algorithm to round\nfloating-point datatypes. For positive "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "decimals"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " it is equivalent to\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "flops.true_divide(flops.rint(a * 10**decimals), 10**decimals)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", which has\nerror due to the inexact representation of decimal fractions in the IEEE\nfloating point standard "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[1]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and errors introduced when scaling by powers\nof ten. For instance, note the extra \"1\" in the following:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round(56294995342131.5, 3)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "56294995342131.51"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If your goal is to print such values with a fixed number of decimals, it is\npreferable to use numpy's float printing routines to limit the number of\nprinted decimals:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.format_float_positional(56294995342131.5, precision=3)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "'56294995342131.5'"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The float printing routines use an accurate but much more computationally\ndemanding algorithm to compute the number of digits after the decimal\npoint."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Alternatively, Python's builtin "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/numpy/rint/",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "rint",
              "text": "round"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " function uses a more accurate\nbut slower algorithm for 64-bit floating point values:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "round(56294995342131.5, 3)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "56294995342131.5"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round(16.055, 2), round(16.055, 2)  # equals 16.0549999999999997"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "(16.06, 16.05)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\n\"Lecture Notes on the Status of IEEE 754\", William Kahan,\nhttps://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~wkahan/ieee754status/IEEE754.PDF",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import flopscope.numpy as fnp"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round([0.37, 1.64])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([0., 2.])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round([0.37, 1.64], decimals=1)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([0.4, 1.6])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round([.5, 1.5, 2.5, 3.5, 4.5]) # rounds to nearest even value"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([0., 2., 2., 4., 4.])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round([1,2,3,11], decimals=1) # ndarray of ints is returned"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([ 1,  2,  3, 11])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "flops.round([1,2,3,11], decimals=-1)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([ 0,  0,  0, 10])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
